# TgBot Project Context

## What is this

Telegram bot on Go for AI access via OpenAI Responses API. Supports text chat, photo analysis, image generation, and image editing. Uses whitelist authorization and in-memory session state.

## Structure

```
cmd/bot/main.go              - entry point
internal/
    config/config.go         - env vars loading
    bot/bot.go               - Bot struct, Run loop, command dispatch
    bot/handlers.go          - text/photo message handling, AI dispatch
    bot/routing.go           - image prefix parsing, intent matchers, size extraction
    bot/send.go              - Telegram send helpers, photo download/encode
    ai/provider.go           - AI provider contract
    ai/openai.go             - OpenAI Responses API client
    session/session.go       - conversation context, previous_response_id, latest image lookup
    auth/whitelist.go        - access control
    logger/logger.go         - logging abstraction (slog implementation)
    version/version.go       - build version info (git commit, date)
```

## Key Dependencies

- `github.com/go-telegram-bot-api/telegram-bot-api/v5` - Telegram
- `github.com/openai/openai-go` - OpenAI Responses API
- `github.com/joho/godotenv` - .env loading

## Configuration (env vars)

- `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` - bot token
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` - API key
- `OPENAI_MODEL` - Responses API model (default: gpt-4o)
- `OPENAI_BASE_URL` - optional compatible API base URL
- `ALLOWED_USERS` - whitelist user_id comma-separated
- `MAX_HISTORY` - max stored messages in session (default: 20)
- `MAX_CONCURRENCY` - max concurrent message handlers (default: 20)
- `LOG_LEVEL` - logging level: debug, info, warn, error (default: info)
- `LOG_FORMAT` - log format: text, json (default: text)

## Bot Commands

- `/start` - welcome
- `/new` - clear context
- `/model` - current model
- `/help` - usage help

## Image Workflows

- Text message -> normal chat, image generation, or image editing based on routing
- Photo message -> photo analysis or image editing based on caption intent
- Reply-to-photo edit flow is supported
- Explicit image prefixes:
  - `img:` / `image:` / `фото:` - force image mode
  - `edit:` / `правь:` - force image edit mode
  - `draw:` / `gen:` - force image generation mode
- Supported image sizes:
  - `1024x1024`
  - `1024x1536`
  - `1536x1024`

